ic byname meaning ‘twin’. The given name has always been popular throughout Christendom, in part because St Thomas's doubts have made him seem a very human character."],"variants":[]},{"name":"de","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Pet form of any of the given names beginning with the letter <i>D-</i> (  compare  Jay   and   Kay  ), in particular   Dorothy .  It is also used as an independent name, and may in some cases be associated with the River Dee (  compare  Clyde  )."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Thomas de Curzon was born about 1152, in Belper, Derbyshire, England, United Kingdom, his father, Richard Curzon, was 29 and his mother, Petronilla de Camville, was 25. He had at least 2 sons with Sybil CURZON DECURZON. He died in England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"about 1152–":"umbes 1152–Surnud","1152–Male":"1152–Surnud","1155–Male":"1155–Surnud","1150–Female":"1150–Surnud","1187–Male":"1187–Surnud","1125–1199":"1125–1199","1129–Female":"1129–Surnud","about 1150":"umbes 1150","1129":"1129","1125":"1125","1199":"1199","1155":"1155","1187":"1187","1152":"1152","1150":"1150","about 1152":"umbes 1152","Kedleston, Bepler, Derbyshire, England":"Kedleston, Derbyshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Kedleston, Derbyshire, England":"Kedleston, Derbyshire, England",",England.":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Belper,Derbyshire,England.":"Belper, Derbyshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1152–":"noin 1152–Kuollut","1152–Male":"1152–Kuollut","1155–Male":"1155–Kuollut","1150–Female":"1150–Kuollut","1187–Male":"1187–Kuollut","1125–1199":"1125–1199","1129–Female":"1129–Kuollut","about 1150":"noin 1150","1129":"1129","1125":"1125","1199":"1199","1155":"1155","1187":"1187","1152":"1152","1150":"1150","about 1152":"noin 1152","Kedleston, Bepler, Derbyshire, England":"Kedleston, Derbyshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Kedleston, Derbyshire, England":"Kedleston, Derbyshire, Engla